+# Solution for Issue #38321
+
+## Root Cause
+
+`SqlServerQueryableMethodTranslatingExpressionVisitor.TransformJsonQueryToTable` looked up
+the JSON container column type-mapping by calling `GetTableMappings()` on the containing entity
+type and then calling `Single()` on the result. When the entity is mapped to a database view
+(via `ToView()`) instead of a table, `GetTableMappings()` returns an empty enumerable, causing
+`Enumerable.Single` to throw `InvalidOperationException: Sequence contains no elements`.
+
+The stack trace in the issue pinpoints this exactly:
+
+```
+at System.Linq.Enumerable.Single[TSource](IEnumerable`1 source)
+at Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SqlServer.Query.Internal
+       .SqlServerQueryableMethodTranslatingExpressionVisitor.TransformJsonQueryToTable(...)
+```
+
+## Change Description
+
+**File:** `src/EFCore.SqlServer/Query/Internal/SqlServerQueryableMethodTranslatingExpressionVisitor.cs`
+
+The three-line lookup was extended to search both table mappings and view mappings before
+calling `Single()`:
+
+```csharp
+// Before
+var containerColumn = structuralType.ContainingEntityType.GetTableMappings()
+    .Select(m => m.Table.FindColumn(containerColumnName))
+    .Single(c => c is not null)!;
+
+// After
+var containingEntityType = structuralType.ContainingEntityType;
+var containerColumn = containingEntityType.GetTableMappings().Cast<ITableMappingBase>()
+    .Concat(containingEntityType.GetViewMappings())
+    .Select(m => m.Table.FindColumn(containerColumnName))
+    .Single(c => c is not null)!;
+```
+
+Both `ITableMapping` and `IViewMapping` extend `ITableMappingBase`, which exposes
+`ITableBase Table { get; }`. `ITableBase.FindColumn(string)` returns `IColumnBase?`, which
+carries the `StoreTypeMapping` property used downstream — so no other callers needed to change.
+
+The variable rename from `entityType` to `containingEntityType` avoids a name collision with
+the `IEntityType entityType` pattern variable in the immediately following `switch` expression.
+
+## Files Edited
+
+- `src/EFCore.SqlServer/Query/Internal/SqlServerQueryableMethodTranslatingExpressionVisitor.cs`
+  — fix: search view mappings in addition to table mappings when resolving the container column.
+
+- `test/EFCore.SqlServer.FunctionalTests/Query/AdHocJsonQuerySqlServerTestBase.cs`
+  — test: `Where_on_json_owned_many_mapped_to_view` exercises the exact scenario from the issue
+  (entity mapped to view with `OwnsMany(...).ToJson()`, filtered with `.Any()`).
+
+## Precedent Usage
+
+1. Query: `"json column view mapped entity GetTableMappings GetViewMappings OPENJSON TransformJsonQueryToTable"`
+   — Result below threshold (score 0.424). Not useful; the returned PR was unrelated scaffolding work.
+
+2. Query: `"TransformJsonQueryToTable view mapping Single no elements"`
+   — Result below threshold (score 0.417). Same unrelated PR returned. Ignored.
+
+No precedent results were relevant; the fix was derived from reading the metadata extension APIs
+(`RelationalTypeBaseExtensions.cs`) and interface hierarchy (`ITableMappingBase`, `IViewMapping`).
